How to Run
Place all files (Main.cpp, RBNode.h, IODialog.h) in one folder.

Open your terminal and cd into that folder.

Compile the program by running:
g++ Main.cpp -o RBTree

Execute the program:

Mac/Linux: ./RBTree

Windows: RBTree.exe

How to use
Menu: Once the program starts, you will see a list of numbered options (1–13).

Input: Type the number of the operation you want to perform and press Enter.

Adding Nodes: Choose option 1, then type your numbers separated by spaces (e.g., 10 5 15) and press Enter.

Project Files
Main.cpp: Runs the menu loop.

RBNode.h: Contains all the Red-Black Tree math, logic, and data structures.

IODialog.h: Manages all the text prompts you see on the screen.